Quickstride snorts and narrows his optics.  He was always ready to kick a 
few enemy heads in.

&quot; Miserable slag headed scrap heaps!  If they think they&#39;re gonna get the 
best of us, Wing Caliber, they&#39;re wrong!  C&#39;mon!  We still have an Ark to 
defend!&quot;

He takes out his largest blast cannon, and quickly charges into battle, 
hoping to wipe out a few unwanted pests.

Meanwhile, deeper into the Ark Tucson uses his own charismatic stealth to 
navigate in the room, thinking what Night Razor may be thinking as well.  He 
uses sharp hearing to pick up the smallest of sounds, even those deemed to 
be completely silent.  He pays close attention to how the ground seems to 
vibrate under his feet, giving him indication that although hidden, he could 
tell where his opponent was.  He slowly brings Straight Shot around.  With 
one of his arms injured, he had to do things in reverse.  With the good arm, 
hold the weight of his weapon, and with the bad arm, pull the trigger.  He 
had often practiced alternating between his hands, and was glad he had done 
so.  Being ambidextrous was an attribute.  He loads an arrow specifically 
designed to be barbed and most difficult to remove.  He knew that it was 
better just to disable his enemy rather than destroy him.  He needed 
Nightrazor for questioning.  Most effective area of targeting, would be the 
knee joint Imbed the arrow in a joint and his opponent would find it most 
difficult to abmulate, yet it would not kill or destroy him.

Now within striking distance, as determined by his sonar sensors, he sends 
out short pulse emissions to pinpoint his area of targeting.  His reading is 
quick, yet, anything could happen at this point.  He aims, and attempts to 
launch an arrow deep into his enemy&#39;s knee, if his calculations were 
correct.

&quot;Steady Straight Shot.  We need to make this count.&quot;

Straight Shot programs her mechanisms for optimal effeciency.

&quot; Talk about a shot in the dark. Okay, let&#39;s do this.&quot;

Outside the Ark, Night Shift quickly scrambles around the enemy fire, 
brought upon by the Sweeps and is quick to cover Rat Trap who is also trying 
to ellude them as well.

&quot;Woah!  Okay, that&#39;s not workn&#39;!  Rat Trap we need a new game plan!&quot;

Rat Trap scurries out of the way of Waspinator&#39;s blasts.

&quot;Gahh!  You&#39;re right!  So, what&#39;dya suppose we do?!&quot;

Night Shift quickly dodges more fire and gets close to Rat Trap, 
transforming into SUV mode on the fly, as he gets his buddy inside his cab.

&quot;First things first, slip inta somethn&#39; with more speed. Whew, at least I 
can dodge better on wheels.&quot;

Rat Trap looks up in the rear view.

&quot;They&#39;re gain&#39;n on us!  C&#39;mon, whatever it is you&#39;re plann&#39;n ta do ya better 
do it fast!&quot;

Night Shift now eyes an area of canyon where it appears to be like a tunnel. 
Large enough for a SUV to speed through, but not large enough for a plane to 
fly through safely.

&quot;Heeeey, I got it.&quot;

Rat Trap catches on.

&quot;Oooohhhh lure &#39;em in but they can&#39;t fly out.  Or through for that matter.. 
Okaaay, I&#39;ll go out on your roof,&#39;n lure &#39;em in, you keep your wheels turn&#39;n 
and try not ta get a flat tire.&quot;

Night Shift opens his window.

&quot;Sounds like a plan ta me.  Okaay, let&#39;s have some fun.&quot;

Rat Trap scurries to his roof, and gets into beast mode.  He soon starts a 
taunting dance to try and lure the enemy his way.

&quot; HEY, AIR HEADS, DOWN HERE!  WE KNOW YA WANT US, SO C&#39;MON, WE DARE YA!&quot;

Night Shift also starts his taunting gestures.

&quot;I know you want a piece of my tailpipe, c&#39;mon, bet your ugly afts ya can&#39;t 
catch me!&quot;

With his wheels, he spins dust and dirt into the air, adding smoke from his 
dual exhaust system for added insult.

